Genesis Startup Competition Pitch - Nanyang Biologics

Stage: WEKA Stage

Recorded on 18 June 2025

transcript.aggregated_text: good afternoon everyone Uh my name is Zui I'm the CTO of of Nanyang Bologics or NYB.AI for short And today we're transforming how we discover new chemical compounds which makes uh drug discovery uh faster safer and more reliable So our company is a spin-off from Nanyang Technological University uh we developed our own proprietary AI model It's called DTIGN It predicts the bioactivity which basically means like how a chemical compound would interact with your body So this helped to uh faster the identifications of high potential natural and synthetic compounds for FGMA and consumer health So what's the problem that we are solving to get a drug asset out to the market it takes around a decade and more than $2 billion of R&D Yet only 10% of it actually make it So traditionally pharma needs to test up to like billions and billions of compounds And so you can see laugh testing is a major cost driver Using O AI we reduce this time from years to just months And this is an issue not with just pharma but also consumer health as well because both built on the backbone of finding the perfect molecules for their drug or applications but they lack the smart tools to pick the right ones So recently both have turned to AI to solve the problems So as of last year almost $10 billion in 12 mega deals was signed between AI uh and big pharma And so just recently some of you might heard about the collaboration between L'Oreal and Nvidia and how they're using AI to supercharge beauty So you may ask like how the hell does AI supercharge beauty right well for us it makes perfect sense because AI can help faster the process of finding the compound interacting with your skin or your body which improve your health and also your beauty So back to our model we train
